+
+
+The construction of the Tower of Babel (historically identified with the Etemenanki ziggurat of Babylon) was not merely an architectural project, but a calculated, system-level breach.[9, 10] The physical structure of the ziggurat acted as a massive resonant antenna designed to interface with a higher operational plane of reality.[9] In systems engineering terms, this represented an unauthorized attempt to bypass established physical and metaphysical boundaries, classified as a rogue process to achieve root administrative access:
